The paper focuses on improving unsupervised document clustering/classification, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), falling under the sub-categories of cs.CL and cs.IR. The use of word embeddings and semantic space also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the mention of software architecture implies a potential focus on systems and information science (cs.SI).
